channel.description:
The Names Brenda :D Ok, I need to know to fix nulls. Example, when i log on my server i spawn some items, and they are called Null.....they have a weird text when i right click and it doesnt do anything when i click it. please tell me how to fix? item.title: Help With Server
item.dc:creator: @brenda brenda
item.description:
@brenda wrote:

[quote=“Mitko, post:19, topic:299588”][quote author=wwe4eva link=topic=395903.msg2943408#msg2943408 date=1252058353]
Dont listen to them, they have no knowledge at all.

This is what is wrong. You are trying to spawn an item that the client doesn’t have models & intergers for. Thereforer it appears as a seed and is called of@’" etc etc.

All you need to do is download the model of the item you are wanting. Extract the models to “models” in the client folder. Copy and paste the intergers which should be supplied underneath item id 2621 in Class8.java – Compile Client. Log onto the server and say the following… add model (model number, e.g 14479) – but say the number that the model is in the winrar. The name of the file.

Hope I helped
[/quote]Looks like mr. knowitall doesnt know and can’t help further XD[/quote]

He actually did help, he even teamviewed with me and did for me caz i couldnt figure it out. if i had stinking 15 rep i would rep him hella…but i cant ;(

item.title: Help With Server
item.dc:creator: @John459 John459
item.description:
@John459 wrote:

To get rid of nulls you must first download rsmv. Once it is downloaded run it then open it. Find the model that is a null and take it out. Next make open it with datmaker and add animation to it if it is a weapon, armor, cape, or clothing. Next make the model files into .dat files and gzip them. Add them into your client models folder and go in game and type your add models command. Then write the ints, compile, and run. You can also download models to make this process faster.
